So I just experienced having some issues with a certain display size in my game. Having the posibility to override the DPI so that getDensity() (which is used throughout the game) returns "fake" values would make debugging layouts and scaling a lot faster.

E.g. having an additional field in LwjglApplicationConfiguration backend:

```
    LwjglApplicationConfiguration cfg = new LwjglApplicationConfiguration();
    cfg.fullscreen = false;
    cfg.resizable = false;
    cfg.width = 480;
    cfg.height = 320;
    cfg.densityOverride = 165;
```

This would essentially emulate a 3.5", 480x320 phone display. It would be much faster and easier than firing up an emulator or acquiring a similar device. Alternatively maybe one could have a field for display size inches? Like `cfg.emulateDisplaySize = 3.5f` would calculate the correct DPI.

Not sure how feasible this would be to implement, but it would sure make creating a multi-display layout easier!
